!! Widget reference

!!! `<$statewrap>`

|!Attribute |!Required |!Description |
|`channels` |Yes |Space-separated channel names (`[a-z0-9-]`) |
|`default-<name>` |No |Default value for channel `<name>`. Omitted channels default to `""` |
|`instid` |No |Instance ID for state isolation. Defaults to TW `qualify` mechanism |

!!! `<$statewrap-rule>`

|!Attribute |!Required |!Description |
|`when` |Yes |Channel name that triggers this rule's actions |

Must be a descendant of `<$statewrap>` (any nesting depth). Contains action widgets that execute when the named channel changes.

!!! `<$action-statewrap-set>`

|!Attribute |!Required |!Description |
|`channel` |Yes |Channel name to write |
|`value` |No |Value to set (defaults to `""`) |
|`no-rules` |No |`"yes"` to skip reactive rules |

!! Filter operator reference

!!! `[statewrap-get[channel]]`

Returns the text value of the named channel's state tiddler. Returns empty if channel not found or no context.

!!! `[statewrap-ref[channel]]`

Returns the state tiddler title (path) for the named channel. Useful for widgets that need a tiddler reference (e.g., `$reveal stateTitle`).

!! State tiddler path format

```
$:/state/rimir/statewrap/<instid>/<channel-name>
```

!! Edge cases

* ''Missing context'' — action widget and filter operators silently no-op if no `<$statewrap>` ancestor exists
* ''Unknown channel'' — logs a console warning, no-op
* ''No cascading'' — `_applyingRules` flag prevents rules from triggering further rules
* ''Shared instid'' — two `<$statewrap>` with the same `instid` share state tiddlers (intentional for cross-widget communication)
* ''Nested statewrap'' — child widgets find the nearest ancestor context

